 able to maintain a distinct identity while simultaneously acculturating to the norms of Iranian society, even taking on significant offices within the Sasanian administration.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChristian converts from Zoroastrianism. 0aChristian martyrszIranxHistoryvSources. 0aManuscripts, Syriac. 0aSassanidsxHistoryvSources. 4aGeneral. 4aHistory. 4aMiddle East. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2023 Part 2z978311117804208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2023 Englishz978311131908708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2023z9783111318110oZDB-23-DGD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertGorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z97831110241270 cprintz978146324487340uhttps://doi.org/10.31826/978146324488040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781463244880423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781463244880/original  a978-3-11-102412-7  Gorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-117804-2  DG Plus PP Package 2023 Part 2b2023  a978-3-11-131908-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGDb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023